This paper is about model pruning, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and computer vision to reduce the size and complexity of neural networks. The paper specifically focuses on using pruning to make the training of neural networks more efficient. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, since the paper involves training ResNet and VGG networks, which are commonly used in neural network research, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, since the paper involves measuring training time and FLOPs (floating point operations per second), which are related to computational efficiency, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a possible sub-category.
